					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Basilica_of_Aparecida_-_Aparecida_2014_(4).jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Basilica_of_Aparecida_-_Aparecida_2014_%284%29.jpg/260px-Basilica_of_Aparecida_-_Aparecida_2014_%284%29.jpg" decoding="async" width="260" height="163" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Basilica_of_Aparecida_-_Aparecida_2014_%284%29.jpg/390px-Basilica_of_Aparecida_-_Aparecida_2014_%284%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Basilica_of_Aparecida_-_Aparecida_2014_%284%29.jpg/520px-Basilica_of_Aparecida_-_Aparecida_2014_%284%29.jpg 2x" data-file-width="2550" data-file-height="1600" /></a><figcaption><a href="/wiki/The_Basilica_of_the_National_Shrine_of_Our_Lady_of_Aparecida" class="mw-redirect" title="The Basilica of the National Shrine of Our Lady of Aparecida">The Basilica of the National Shrine of Our Lady of Aparecida</a> in <a href="/wiki/Aparecida" title="Aparecida">Aparecida</a>, <a href="/wiki/Brazil" title="Brazil">Brazil</a> It is the second largest church in the world, after <a href="/wiki/St._Peter%27s_Basilica" title="St. Peter&#39;s Basilica">St. Peter's Basilica</a> in <a href="/wiki/Vatican_City" title="Vatican City">Vatican City</a>.</figcaption></figure>
